The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Indians begin in style

Pune: India?s elite cueists started their campaign in style with convincing wins on the opening day of the fourth Asian billiards meet at the PYC Hindu Gymkhana here on Sunday. 

Defending champion Devendra Joshi set the ball rolling with a 3-0 rout of Wan-Sun Lee of Singapore that included a 95 break in the opening frame. 

Seven-time world professional champion Geet Sethi rifled in a superb unfinished run of 104 in the first frame on way to a 3-1 rout of Myanmar?s Khin Mg Oo in another group A match. Double Asian games gold-medallist Ashok Shandilya rallied from an opening game loss to dispatch Imran Shahzad of Pakistan 3-1 in a group C tie, powered by an unfinished 101 break in the fourth frame. 

B. Bhaskar and national champion Pankaj Advani completed a fine opening day for the hosts with easy 3-0 wins in group B. (PTI) 




